<h2>&#x2753; Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Is it safe to buy crypto during a crash?</h3>
<p>Yes, if you use a reputable exchange and secure storage. Avoid FOMO ” systematic buying is safer than panic buying. Always transfer significant holdings to a hardware wallet.</p>

<h3>Which exchange has the lowest fees for buying BTC?</h3>
<p>Binance with BNB fee deduction (0.075%) is the lowest among major exchanges. Coinbase charges 0.6% standard but drops to 0.4% on Advanced Trade. KuCoin charges 0.1%.</p>

<h3>Should I buy BTC or SOL during the dip?</h3>
<p>Bitcoin historically recovers first, then altcoins follow. A 70/30 BTC/SOL split is a common strategy. Meme coins carry higher risk but higher potential reward in a recovery.</p>

<h3>Can I use multiple exchanges for dip buying?</h3>
<p>Absolutely ” recommended. Keep funds on 2-3 exchanges so you can buy wherever liquidity is deepest and fees are lowest at the moment.</p>

